    <h1 class="post-title">About</h1>
    <div class="post-rule"></div>
  </header>
  <div class="post-body">
    <p>
      Zero Parsec is where I write about things worth understanding slowly. The subjects change — human nature, motorsport, culture, technology, the way ideas move through the world and what happens to them in transit. What stays constant is the method: start with a question, follow it honestly, write it up only when the thinking is actually done.
    </p>

    <p>
      The name comes from the idea of a starting point. The distance between not knowing and knowing, measured from the beginning. Most of what appears here starts there — as something half-formed, argued with in my head, not yet resolved. Writing is how the resolution happens, or doesn't. Either way, it ends up here.
    </p>
  </div>
</article>
